{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1778207839,"nonce":"+Jy6z1PE+u9vl8DEOcS0Ok9MhM4=","title":"CLAUDE.md: add RunPod deploy runbook for rlrmp experiments","message":"**Trigger.** During the flavor-(b) smoke-test setup, the agent had to rediscover (and partially relearn the hard way) the steps for running rlrmp training on RunPod that were already worked out in Part 2.5: which path-deps need to be synced, how to handle SSH-session-killed installs, what GPUs work, etc.\n\n**The runbook should cover** (minimal but complete):\n\n1. **Prerequisites:**\n   - Install `runpodctl` (binary download from GitHub releases; the install.sh requires sudo).\n   - SSH key at `~/.runpod/ssh/RunPod-Key-Go`.\n   - API key in `~/.runpod/config.toml` (configure via `runpodctl config --apiKey ...` if missing).\n\n2. **Pre-flight checks** (cross-ref dotfiles `3602840` + comment): verify image manifest exists on Docker Hub before `pod create`; verify GPU availability per DC via `runpodctl datacenter list`.\n\n3. **GPU choice** (cross-ref subagent analysis): RTX 4090 for validated/cheapest; RTX 5090 for Blackwell speedup with caveat that some templates have stale image references. Use `runpod/pytorch:1.0.3-cu1281-torch290-ubuntu2204` (or newer cu1290/cu1300) for Blackwell support — skip the deprecated `runpod/pytorch:2.8.0-...` template.\n\n4. **Deploy steps** (the load-bearing part):\n   1. `pod create --image \"\u003cverified image\u003e\" --gpu-id \"NVIDIA GeForce RTX 5090\" --data-center-ids EUR-IS-2 --cloud-type SECURE --container-disk-in-gb 30 --volume-in-gb 30` (or 4090 + community).\n   2. Poll for SSH ready via `runpodctl pod get \u003cid\u003e`'s `runtime.ports` field. Bail if no progress in ~3 min.\n   3. **rsync 3 path-deps to /workspace** (excluding `_artifacts`, `worktrees`, `.venv`):\n      - rlrmp main → `/workspace/rlrmp/`\n      - feedbax/worktrees/develop → `/workspace/feedbax/`\n      - 05 Utils/jax-cookbook (excluding `worktrees` — 480 MB) → `/workspace/jax-cookbook/`\n   4. **Patch the embedded paths** on the pod (sed, in pyproject.toml AND uv.lock for both rlrmp and feedbax):\n      - rlrmp/pyproject.toml: feedbax path → `/workspace/feedbax`\n      - rlrmp/uv.lock: jax-cookbook editable → `/workspace/jax-cookbook`\n      - **feedbax/pyproject.toml**: jax-cookbook path → `/workspace/jax-cookbook` (this is the one that's easy to forget — feedbax also has its own jax-cookbook path-dep that uv resolves transitively)\n      - feedbax/uv.lock: jax-cookbook editable → `/workspace/jax-cookbook`\n   5. `uv sync` from `/workspace/rlrmp/`.\n   6. `uv pip install -U \"jax[cuda12]\"` (the pyproject doesn't pin the CUDA-enabled jaxlib; it must be added explicitly). Allow ~3–5 min on slow links.\n\n5. **Long-running setup commands must survive SSH disconnect**: run via `nohup ... \u0026` with output redirected to a logfile, then poll `/workspace/install_done` marker. SSH session interrupted while `uv pip install` is in progress → SIGHUP kills the install → wasted bandwidth. nohup avoids this.\n\n6. **Smoke test command**: `uv run python scripts/train_minimax.py --adversary-type linear_dynamics --n-warmup-batches 3 --n-adversary-batches 20 --adv-batch-size 250 --n-replicates 5 --hidden-type gru --output-dir /workspace/smoke_test --checkpoint --fused` (or matching the latest config).\n\n7. **Monitoring cadence** (per user's standing instruction):\n   - Smoke test: 1 min after start, then every 5 min.\n   - Full run: 1 min until JIT compilation visible, every 5 min during early loss decline, drop to every 30 min once loss is steadily descending.\n   Always watch for `ptxas` / `OOM` / `Traceback` patterns alongside the loss-progress signal.\n\n8. **Cost discipline**: pod billing starts on creation, not on container start. Verify `uptimeSeconds \u003e 0` within 2 min of creation; bail if stuck. Don't unilaterally upgrade cloud tier or GPU class — ask first (cross-ref dotfiles `3602840`).\n\n**Placement in CLAUDE.md**: new section after `## Feedbax Integration`, titled `## RunPod Deploy Runbook for rlrmp Experiments`. Aim for ~1 page.\n\n**Why this matters**: future agents (or future-me) re-running training will save 30+ minutes per session and avoid burning ~$0.20+ on stuck pods. Currently this knowledge lives only in the Part 2.5 session log, which is hard to find.","files":null}]}